The only small problem was that our room was not ready at check in, but they switched our floors and brought us to a room as quickly as possible.	I was able to negotiate a late check-out (2pm, not that great) and they gave us a bottle of sparkling wine but that's about it.	We decided to check out for two days for a quick visit to Whistler and the hotel offered to keep some or our luggage so that we could travel lightly.	With the Wedgewood I always feel like I'm visiting family, and the box of chocolates at check-in and nightly turn down service with a bottle of water and some cookies sure does help that along!